Kano State Governor Dr Abdullahi Umar Ganduje on Thursday queried Emir Muhammadu Sanusi II on Thursday over allegations of fund misappropriation. The Kano State Anti-Corruption and Public Complaint Commission on Monday indicted the emir and recommended his suspension. The Chief of Staff to the Emir, Munir Sanusi, who confirmed the receipt of the query, said the state government sought the response of the emir within 24 hours regarding allegations of misappropriation of funds. “We received the query today (Thursday). The state government has demanded the response of His Highness within 24 hours. The council is studying the content,” he said. Details shortly…